issues.title: E-Gear Transmission Failure
issues.description: The ISR (Independent Shifting Rods) single-clutch automated manual transmission is prone to failure, particularly the actuators and hydraulic system. Common failures include gear selection issues, jerky shifts, and complete transmission lockup.
issues.fix_description: Replace transmission actuators, hydraulic pumps, or complete transmission rebuild depending on failure extent
issues.prevention: Regular transmission fluid changes, avoid aggressive driving when cold, proper warm-up procedures

issues.title: Engine Lifter Failure
issues.description: The V12 engine suffers from hydraulic lifter failures, particularly affecting cylinders 2, 4, 6, 8, 10, and 12. This can lead to catastrophic engine damage if not addressed promptly.
issues.fix_description: Replace affected lifters, potentially requiring engine removal and complete top-end rebuild
issues.prevention: Use high-quality oil, maintain proper oil change intervals, avoid cold engine redlining

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Body Panel Delamination
issues.description: Carbon fiber panels, particularly the roof and side panels, experience delamination where layers separate. This affects structural integrity and aesthetics.
symptoms: Visible separation in carbon fiber weave
issues.fix_description: Replace affected carbon fiber panels, requires specialized carbon fiber repair techniques
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperature fluctuations, proper storage conditions, regular inspection

issues.title: Magnetorheological Damper Failure
issues.description: The adaptive suspension system's magnetorheological dampers fail, causing loss of ride quality control and potential safety issues. Rear dampers are particularly prone to failure.
issues.fix_description: Replace failed dampers with OEM or upgraded aftermarket units
issues.prevention: Avoid harsh impacts, regular suspension inspection, proper wheel alignment

issues.title: Electronic Control Unit (ECU) Failures
issues.description: Various ECUs throughout the vehicle fail, including engine management, transmission control, and body control modules. This can cause multiple system malfunctions.
issues.fix_description: Replace failed ECU modules and reprogram vehicle systems
issues.prevention: Avoid electrical overloads, maintain proper battery voltage, protect from moisture

issues.title: Clutch Actuator Failure
issues.description: The hydraulic clutch actuator in the ISR transmission fails, preventing proper clutch engagement and disengagement. This is separate from but related to transmission issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace clutch actuator assembly and hydraulic components
issues.prevention: Proper transmission warm-up, avoid aggressive launches when cold, regular fluid maintenance

issues.title: Exhaust Manifold Cracking
issues.description: The exhaust manifolds on the V12 engine develop cracks due to thermal stress, leading to exhaust leaks and potential performance issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace cracked exhaust manifolds with improved design units
issues.prevention: Allow proper engine warm-up and cool-down cycles, avoid thermal shock

issues.title: Air Conditioning Compressor Failure
issues.description: The A/C compressor fails prematurely, often due to refrigerant leaks or electrical issues. Common in high-temperature climates.
issues.fix_description: Replace A/C compressor, condenser, and refrigerant system components
issues.prevention: Regular A/C system maintenance, check refrigerant levels annually

issues.title: Fuel System Issues
issues.description: Fuel pump failures and fuel injector problems cause performance issues and potential engine damage. Often related to fuel quality and system contamination.
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pumps, injectors, or fuel system cleaning depending on issue
issues.prevention: Use high-quality fuel, regular fuel system cleaning, replace fuel filters

issues.title: Cooling System Leaks
issues.description: Various cooling system components including radiators, hoses, and water pumps develop leaks, potentially leading to overheating issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace failed cooling system components and pressure test system
issues.prevention: Regular coolant changes, inspect hoses and connections, maintain proper coolant levels

issues.title: Interior Electronic Malfunctions
issues.description: Various interior electronic components fail including infotainment system, climate control, and instrument cluster displays.
issues.fix_description: Replace or repair specific electronic modules and displays
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperatures, protect from moisture, regular system updates

editorial.tagline: V12 fury wrapped in carbon fiber perfection
editorial.hero_blurb: The Aventador LP 700-4 represents Lamborghini's purest expression of the naturally aspirated V12 supercar. With its angular design language and howling 6.5-liter heart, this is automotive theater at its most dramatic.
editorial.essence: This is the last of the great naturally aspirated Lamborghini V12s, delivering 700 horsepower through a symphony of mechanical precision. The Aventador combines fighter jet aesthetics with old-school supercar drama that modern turbocharged engines simply cannot replicate.
editorial.heritage: Launched in 2011 as the successor to the legendary Murci√©lago, the Aventador carries forward Lamborghini's tradition of V12 flagship supercars. Named after a fighting bull, it represents the final evolution of Lamborghini's naturally aspirated V12 era before hybridization.
editorial.design_philosophy: Chief designer Filippo Perini created an angular masterpiece inspired by stealth fighter jets and crystalline geometry. Every surface serves aerodynamic purpose while maintaining Lamborghini's signature aggression and visual drama.
editorial.motorsport_history: While primarily a road car, the Aventador spawned track-focused variants and formed the basis for Lamborghini's Super Trofeo racing series, proving its performance credentials on circuits worldwide.
editorial.engine_character: The 6.5L V12 is a naturally aspirated masterpiece that builds power linearly and dramatically. It feels alive, vibrating through the cabin with mechanical intensity that turbocharged engines cannot match, delivering power with visceral immediacy.
editorial.transmission_feel: The single-clutch ISR transmission is brutally fast but lacks refinement in traffic. In Corsa mode, shifts are violent and race-car sharp, while Strada mode offers more civility without losing the mechanical drama.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The carbon fiber monocoque provides incredible rigidity while the pushrod suspension delivers surprisingly compliant ride quality. The chassis feels unshakeable at speed, with predictable handling characteristics enhanced by the all-wheel-drive system.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulically assisted steering offers genuine feedback and proper weight. The steering communicates road surface and grip levels clearly, though it can feel heavy at parking speeds - a worthy trade-off for high-speed precision.
editorial.brake_confidence: Massive carbon-ceramic brakes provide fade-free stopping power with excellent pedal feel. The brakes inspire complete confidence even during track use, with linear response and remarkable heat resistance.
editorial.sound_signature: The V12 produces an otherworldly wail that starts as a rumble and builds to a spine-tingling crescendo at 8,000 RPM. The exhaust note is pure mechanical music - raw, unfiltered, and absolutely intoxicating.
editorial.ideal_owner: Collectors and enthusiasts who value naturally aspirated drama over outright lap times. Perfect for those who want the full sensory supercar experience and appreciate mechanical purity over modern convenience.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Daily drivers seeking comfort and practicality. The single-clutch transmission and firm ride make traffic duty challenging, while limited storage space restricts practical use.
editorial.buyers_summary: Buy the cleanest, lowest-mileage example you can afford - these are appreciating classics. The 2013+ models received minor improvements, but any Aventador LP 700-4 represents the pinnacle of naturally aspirated V12 engineering.
